Enallagma cyathigerum is a species of damselfly belonging to the family Coenagrionidae. 
It is commonly known as the common blue damselfly. 
The male has bright blue coloration on its head and thorax but has black markings on its abdomen. 
It has a slender and elongated shape, with a wingspan of about 3-4 cm. 
Females have a slightly different coloration, with a more green/blue hue on their thorax. 
They can be found near freshwater habitats, such as ponds, lakes, and slow-moving streams. 
Enallagma cyathigerum is commonly distributed throughout Europe and parts of Asia.
